<br>
51 Rogue (me)<br>
50 Druid<br>
50 Wizard<br>
48 Monk<br>
47 Enchanter<br>
46 Mage<br>
<br>
+ maybe a 51 mage and 49 cleric if they happen to be available.<br>
<br>
On several occasions, for some big mobs the wizard has snared and spammed his Staff of Temparate Flux on the mob for a minute or so before I jump behind it and follow along backstabbing.  For those that don't know, the Staff has an instant cast minor resistance debuff effect.  The aggro per cast has been long since nerfed, but there is still a small amount, and if he keeps it up as he kites around, it adds up and the mobs generally ignore any pets or melee characters running behind hitting them.  <br>
<br>
My thoughts are that I'll have everyone sow'ed, spawn her, get the druid to run her around until he can get an ensnare to stick.  (ensnare lasts 10 minutes or so)  The wizard can then spam the living hell out of her with the staff for a minute or so, and the melee types and pets will follow and beat her up, with the druid thowing in nukes and dot's as necessary, or perhaps just standing by for emergency heals.<br>
<br>
Does she have any unusual aggro characteristics that would prevent this from working?  I'm thinking it's safe enough - since no one engages until she is snared, so that even if she does aggro on someone else they can probably get away from her quickly enough until aggro is regained on the kiter.  <br>
<br>
Or, should I not even bother with melee types getting close, and just snare her and run her around getting nuked and dot'd?  Aggro would bounce around, so everyone would have to be very careful not to get hit, since she packs such a punch.<br>
<br>
Any opinions on the best way to accomplish this with the above group is appreciated!  I REALLY don't want to risk failing this and having to re-do the quest.<br>
<br>
Lorace<br>
51 Rogue, E Marr<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzania.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zania</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 2:11:06 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Renux strategy -  will it work?</span><hr size=1> It will be really hard for a druid to land snare at that level, but otherwise no problem.  Dont really need wizzy either, just make druid chain cast snare on her, worked fine for my friend.<br>
<br>
Zania <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/udurden.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Durden</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/anim_1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Safehouse Supporter</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/2/01 1:54:28 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Renux strategy -  will it work?</span><hr size=1> My advice, since you don't have a warrior to tank.  Pay for everyone to get Dead Man Floating.<br>
<br>
Use a Spine Break poison, or the snare poison.  You'll have a greater chance of getting your poison to stick then the druid staying alive long enough to get snare to stick.<br>
<br>
Hell, the wizzie has 3-4 stuns they could possibly use.  You may just want to chain stun her and have everyone else beat her down.<br>
<br>
But my advice, is to use a poison to snare before trying to do anything else.<br>
<br>
 <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzanoan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zanoan </A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/3/01 12:33:02 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Renux strategy -  will it work?</span><hr size=1> nm : ) <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uzanoan.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Zanoan </A> at: 10/3/01 12:33:27 am<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/upathfinder101.showPublicProfile?language=EN>pathfinder101</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/3/01 2:03:17 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Renux strategy -  will it work?</span><hr size=1>  I was 54(ranger) at the time we tried her for a rogue friend. i could not get ensnare to stick, ever. You may get lucky or we may have had just bad luck.  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/ugalaintreeavenger.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Galain Treeavenger</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/3/01 2:17:24 pm)</font><br>     <br>Community Supporter<br> </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Renux strategy -  will it work?</span><hr size=1> This is what I would do with your available people.  Spawn renux and have the druid snare, not ensnare, Renux about 10 times.  If it sticks, Great.  If not, have the enchanter Tash her, but make sure the druid is constantly casting snare on her while the enchanter tries to land a Tash.  Must keep the agro on the druid.<br>
<br>
Once she is tashed or snared or both, have the druid kite her around, making sure he stays within agro range, and cast snare pretty much continuously.  The druid can throw a dot on if their mana will be fine for keeping the agro.  <br>
<br>
While the druid is kiting, all melees beat the crap out of her from behind.  Get the hell away if you somehow gain agro though.  The Wiz can begin nuking when she is at 50% I think.  I am unsure on that since I usually do it with me as the only caster casting on her. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umalse.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Malse</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/3/01 3:29:55 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Renux strategy -  will it work?</span><hr size=1> It works, yes.<br>
<br>
The wizard staff is the best aggro kiting tool in the game. Screw druids :&gt; You'll have trouble sticking snare or anything else, though. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/umerristealshearts.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Merri Stealshearts</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/4/01 6:41:04 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Renux strategy -  will it work?</span><hr size=1> pretty much what they all said. The unpleasant habit you need to be aware of is that if somehow the kiter loses agro, say bye-bye to the poor SoB who got it, unless they're a rogue or monk. Jolt has never worked on her to my knowledge, evade is a lucky shot but it HAS worked, and FD usually lands if successful. <br>
<br>
Renux &quot;frenzies&quot; on someone if they try to toe-to-toe her with agro. For this reason, the fear-kite method used  to be the way to do her, but now kiting seems to be pretty much it, unless you want to go the &quot;big tank-cleric&quot; combo with chain healing. Also be aware, that this method is BOUND to get either your rogue or one of your casters killed. I've never yet met a warrior who would keep Renux' attention for the whole fight.<br>
<br>
Merribelle Stealshearts, 60<br>
~shadowy scheherazade~<br>
Cry of War, Bristlebane <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/utaurkon.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Taurkon</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/4/01 2:07:52 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Renux strategy -  will it work?</span><hr size=1> Seeing as how this is a big step in your epic, my recommendation is find more friends of a higher level.  If everything goes perfect, you might win.  If Renux drops one or two of you, it will be all over.  Go do KC and ask if some peeps will help.  Have TP's arranged to GFay or BB, and offer everyone booze.  I almost lost to Renux with a group much better than yours.  Our 59 Pally went down in seconds, and the Mage dropped too.  The only thing that saved our ass was the fact the chanter got a slow off on Renux.<br>
<br>
GL<br>
  Taurkon <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#3B3B3B><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub13.ezboard.com/uskob.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Skob</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(10/5/01 9:47:46 am)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Renux strategy -  will it work?</span><hr size=1> Thanks for all the feedback.  I believe I'm going to let my druid friend get a few more levels so that he has a better chance to land snare quickly, and then have the wizard kite her with the Staff of Temparate Flux as we follow.  We've tested the staff on a few high level kills recently, and Malse is right - if you use it correctly, it is almost impossible to get the aggro off the wizard no matter what you do, as long as no one does something stupid.<br>
